Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of theorem provers, which is a common tool in artificial intelligence research, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of propositional modal logic, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory, making cs.PL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a method for reasoning, which falls under the category of software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category as well.
